---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = '/tradfi-onchain';
---

<Layout title="Prop Trading — Onchain Strategies">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-24">
    <p class="text-cyan-400 text-sm font-medium tracking-wider uppercase mb-4">
      <span class="lang-en">Prop Trading</span><span class="lang-zh">自營交易</span>
    </p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white leading-tight mb-8">
      <span class="lang-en">Onchain Trading Strategies for Prop Desks</span>
      <span class="lang-zh">自營交易部門的鏈上交易策略</span>
    </h1>

    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-zinc max-w-none text-zinc-400 text-[15px] leading-relaxed space-y-6">

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">In January 2026, trading volume on perpetual futures for traditional assets — stocks, commodities, indices — hit $31 billion on Hyperliquid alone, a 162% increase from $11.8 billion the previous month. Open interest across pre-IPO stock perps reached $1.43 billion. These numbers are not from a niche exchange: Hyperliquid processes $5 to $10 billion in daily volume across all markets, on par with Bybit and OKX.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">2026年1月，僅在Hyperliquid上，傳統資產 — 股票、商品、指數 — 的永續合約交易量就達到$310億，較上月的$118億增長162%。Pre-IPO股票永續合約的未平倉量達到$14.3億。這些數字不是來自小型交易所：Hyperliquid在所有市場的日交易量為$50至$100億，與Bybit和OKX同級。</span>
      </p>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">For prop trading desks, onchain markets offer a set of strategy opportunities that simply don't exist in traditional markets — not as an alternative to what you already do, but as an additional set of instruments with distinct structural characteristics.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">對自營交易部門而言，鏈上市場提供了一組傳統市場根本不存在的策略機會 — 不是作為你已有業務的替代，而是一組具有獨特結構特徵的額外工具。</span>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-16 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">Pre-IPO Stock Perps</span><span class="lang-zh">Pre-IPO股票永續合約</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">Hyperliquid's HIP-3 protocol, launched in October 2025, enables permissionless deployment of perpetual futures markets. Platforms built on HIP-3 — like Ventuals — offer perp exposure to private company valuations: SpaceX, OpenAI, Anthropic, Cursor, Stripe. These are not equity instruments; they are pure valuation speculation contracts that settle against the latest funding round price or IPO price.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">Hyperliquid的HIP-3協議於2025年10月推出，允許無需許可地部署永續合約市場。基於HIP-3構建的平台 — 如Ventuals — 提供對私營公司估值的永續合約敞口：SpaceX、OpenAI、Anthropic、Cursor、Stripe。這些不是股權工具；它們是純估值投機合約，以最新融資輪價格或IPO價格結算。</span>
      </p>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">Leverage is up to 10x — lower than crypto perps due to lower underlying liquidity. But the volume tells the story: pre-IPO perps now represent over 35% of all Hyperliquid trading volume. This is not a niche product.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">槓桿最高10x — 因底層流動性較低，比crypto永續合約低。但交易量說明了一切：Pre-IPO永續合約現佔Hyperliquid總交易量的35%以上。這不是小眾產品。</span>
      </p>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">The edge for finance professionals is obvious. If you're in investment banking, private equity, or venture capital, you see deal flow, write valuations, and meet management teams. Your sector knowledge and valuation insight is directly monetizable here — you're trading against retail participants who don't have your information advantage. The caveat is equally obvious: this is not regulated by the SFC, and there is no deposit protection.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">金融專業人士的優勢顯而易見。如果你在投資銀行、私募股權或風險投資行業，你看到交易流、撰寫估值報告、見管理團隊。你的行業知識和估值洞察力可以直接在此變現 — 你在與不具備你信息優勢的散戶交易。同樣顯而易見的是：這不受SFC監管，且沒有存款保障。</span>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-16 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">Funding Rate Arbitrage</span><span class="lang-zh">資金費率套利</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">Perpetual futures use a funding rate to keep the contract price anchored to spot. When funding is positive, longs pay shorts; when negative, shorts pay longs. The rate varies across exchanges — Binance pays every 8 hours, Hyperliquid every hour — creating persistent basis differentials.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">永續合約使用資金費率使合約價格錨定現貨。當資金費率為正時，多方支付空方；當為負時，空方支付多方。費率在各交易所之間有差異 — Binance每8小時支付一次，Hyperliquid每小時一次 — 造成持續的基差差異。</span>
      </p>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">The classic strategy: go long spot, short perp (or vice versa), capturing the funding rate differential as yield while maintaining delta-neutral price exposure. A November 2025 research paper analyzing 35.7 million observations across 749 symbols and 26 exchanges found that symbols with an average spread of 20 basis points or more yielded a theoretical 219% APY. The reality is more tempered: only about 40% of top opportunities generated positive returns after transaction costs and spread reversals. But for desks with the infrastructure to monitor and execute across venues, the opportunity set is substantial.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">經典策略：做多現貨、做空永續合約（或反之），在維持價格delta中性的同時捕獲資金費率差異作為收益。2025年11月一篇分析了26個交易所、749個交易對、3,570萬個觀測值的研究論文發現，平均價差20個基點以上的交易對理論年化收益率為219%。現實更為溫和：在交易成本和價差回歸後，僅約40%的頂級機會產生正回報。但對於擁有跨平台監控和執行基礎設施的部門，機會集是可觀的。</span>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-16 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">AMM Liquidity Provision</span><span class="lang-zh">AMM流動性提供</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">Providing liquidity to an automated market maker is, in finance terms, being long two assets and short volatility. You deposit token pairs into a pool, earn trading fees from every swap, and accept impermanent loss — the cost of the implicit short vol position — when prices diverge.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">向自動化做市商提供流動性，用金融語言來說，就是做多兩種資產加做空波動率。你將代幣對存入池中，從每筆交易中賺取費用，並在價格偏離時承受無常損失 — 即隱含做空波動率倉位的成本。</span>
      </p>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">Stablecoin pairs (USDC/USDT) offer 0.01 to 0.05% per swap with minimal impermanent loss — comparable to money market yields. New token launches can carry fee rates of 50 to 99%, generating significant short-term returns when volume is high, though the underlying tokens are extremely volatile and frequently go to zero. A 2025 MEXC Research study found that 54.7% of Uniswap V3 LPs in volatile pairs lost money, and only 37.2% of non-stablecoin positions ended in profit. Concentrated liquidity positions — where LPs pick a specific price band — can massively increase fee capture within that range, but require active management.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">穩定幣對（USDC/USDT）每筆交易提供0.01至0.05%的費用，無常損失最小 — 與貨幣市場收益相當。新代幣發行可有50至99%的費率，在交易量高時產生可觀的短期回報，但底層代幣波動極大且經常歸零。2025年MEXC Research研究發現，Uniswap V3波動對中54.7%的LP虧損，僅37.2%的非穩定幣倉位盈利。集中流動性倉位 — LP選擇特定價格區間 — 可大幅增加該區間內的費用捕獲，但需要主動管理。</span>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-16 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">Who Is Already Here</span><span class="lang-zh">誰已在此</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">The firms trading onchain are not startups. Jump Trading — one of the largest high-frequency trading firms in traditional markets — has over $300 million in on-chain holdings on Ethereum alone and has built custom MEV and arbitrage infrastructure across all major blockchains. Wintermute handles $5 billion or more in daily trading volume, provides liquidity across 50-plus exchanges, and generated 11% of Robinhood's transaction-based revenue in early 2025. Cumberland, the crypto arm of DRW Holdings (a 30-year-old prop trading firm), serves Goldman Sachs, Bloomberg, and major hedge funds. Citadel Securities — the world's largest equities market maker — has invested $200 million in Kraken and is expanding into crypto market making.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">在鏈上交易的公司不是初創企業。Jump Trading — 傳統市場最大的高頻交易公司之一 — 僅在Ethereum上就持有超過$3億的鏈上資產，並在所有主要區塊鏈上建立了定制的MEV和套利基礎設施。Wintermute日交易量超$50億，在50多個交易所提供流動性，並在2025年初貢獻了Robinhood 11%的交易相關收入。Cumberland是DRW Holdings（一家有30年歷史的自營交易公司）的加密部門，服務Goldman Sachs、Bloomberg和主要對沖基金。Citadel Securities — 全球最大的股票做市商 — 已投資$2億於Kraken並正在擴展至加密做市。</span>
      </p>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">The infrastructure requirements are non-trivial: low-latency RPC/gRPC nodes for blockchain state access, SWQoS (Stake-Weighted Quality of Service) on Solana or Flashbots on Ethereum for priority transaction landing, real-time monitoring of pool states and funding rates, and risk management frameworks that account for smart contract risk, impermanent loss, and liquidation cascades. But for desks willing to invest in the tooling, the strategy space is wide open — and the competition, while intensifying, is still orders of magnitude less dense than traditional markets.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">基礎設施需求不容小覷：用於區塊鏈狀態訪問的低延遲RPC/gRPC節點、Solana上的SWQoS（質押加權服務質量）或Ethereum上的Flashbots用於優先交易落地、實時監控池狀態和資金費率，以及考慮智能合約風險、無常損失和清算級聯的風險管理框架。但對於願意投資工具的部門，策略空間是完全開放的 — 而競爭雖在加劇，密度仍比傳統市場低幾個數量級。</span>
      </p>
    </div>

